Package: MatchingFrontier
Version: 4.1.0.9000
Type: Package
Title: Computation of the Balance-Sample Size Frontier in Matching Methods for Causal Inference
Authors@R: c(
  person("Gary", "King", email = "king@harvard.edu", role = c("aut"),
         comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5327-7631")),
  person("Christopher", "Lucas", email = "christopher.lucas@wustl.edu", role = c("aut")),
  person("Richard", "Nielsen", email = "rnielsen@mit.edu", role = c("aut")),
  person("Noah", "Greifer", role = c("aut", "cre"), 
         email = "ngreifer@iq.harvard.edu",
	       comment = c(ORCID="0000-0003-3067-7154"))
  )
Description: Returns the subset of the data with the minimum imbalance for 
	     every possible subset size (N - 1, N - 2, ...), down to the data set with the 
	     minimum possible imbalance. Also includes tools for the estimation
	     of causal effects for each subset size, functions for visualization
	     and data export, and functions for calculating
	     model dependence. 
URL: https://projects.iq.harvard.edu/frontier, https://iqss.github.io/MatchingFrontier
BugReports: https://github.com/IQSS/MatchingFrontier/issues
